headline: Boeing Sells Jeppesen Unit to Thoma Bravo for $10.6 Billion
summary: (Bloomberg) -- Boeing Co. agreed to sell its flight navigation unit and other digital assets to Thoma Bravo for $10.6 billion in cash, the first major portfolio transaction under Chief Executive Officer Kelly Ortberg as he seeks to shore up the planemaker’s finances.
